Unknown to many, the Philippines has been an active player in <a href="http://www.rappler.com/brandrap/stories/98207-bpo-philippines-timeline">the outsourcing industry</a> since the early 1990's. Its exponential growth in this decade has resulted in the country topping the list as a <a href="http://www.manilatimes.net/philippines-the-new-call-center-capital-of-the-world/47984/">prime outsourcing location</a> in 2010.

&nbsp;

One of the main reasons why the Philippines is a top choice for foreign companies is the countryâ€™s compatibility with Western Culture.

The Philippines is one of the worldâ€™s largest English-speaking nations. In fact, the country has topped the Business English Index, a whitepaper released by Global English, for two consecutive years for English competency in the workplace.

As English is the primary language of business, it is easy to see why many international global outsourcing companies hire qualified staff from the Philippines.
